title.narrative: By 2020, the government has an improved capacity to design, implement, monitor and coordinate policies and strategies related to multi-sectoral nutrition (MSN) interventions.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported delivery of key nutrition interventions convenient with context of Covid-19. Treatment of severe acute malnourished children has been taken to scale in 67 targeted districts (both development and emergency contexts) in Far-North, North, Adamawa and East regions. This was extended to South-West and North-West regions. Home fortification program with micronutrient powders has expanded from 25 health districts (2019) to 35 (2020). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
